					<head>Sefer ha-emunah ha-ramah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947" rend="visible">
						<summary>Sefer ha-emunah ha-ramah by Abraham ben David ibn Daud, translated from Arabic to Hebrew by Shelomoh ben Labi.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947">
							<locus from="1r" to="130v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר האמונה הרמה</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-emunah ha-ramah</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/86518157">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/86518157" xml:lang="en">Ibn Daud, Abraham ben David,, Halevi, approximately 1110-approximately 1180</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/86518157" xml:lang="he">אברהם בן דוד, הלוי, ראב"ד </persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Cf. <ref target="Neubauer_1994" type="number">1227</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper and parchment codex; Sefardi semi-cursive script of 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="mixed">
								<support>Paper and parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>130 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>133</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>130 folios (+ 1 modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>First leaf slightly damaged.</p>
									<p>One leaf missing after folio 119.</p>
									<p>Paper leaves slightly water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible horizontal and vertical ruling with pencil on the paper leaves. Flesh side and hair side distinguishable on the vellum leaves.</p>
									<p>Initial words of each section written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords given only occasionally. The last word of the folio is usually repeated at the beginning of the next folio.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Black buckram, blind tooled.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Abraham b. David. Emunah Ramah. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 1069.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
